NHL ENTRY DRAFT
June 27, 1998
Jeff Heerema
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT








JEFF HEEREMA:  I can't even explain it.  I am really happy about it.


Q.  (inaudible)

JEFF HEEREMA:  Anywhere in the first round would have been great.  I came in 13th.  I am really happy.


Q.  (inaudible)

JEFF HEEREMA:  My parents and my two brothers and my agent.


Q.  (inaudible)

JEFF HEEREMA:  No, we flew down to Minneapolis and then to here.


Q.  Great year for you?

JEFF HEEREMA:  Yeah, it has been pretty hectic, but I have gotten used to it and I mean, it comes with the game and I have come to enjoy it.


Q.  (inaudible)

JEFF HEEREMA:  I think I am a pretty fast skater, like to get in the corners and go for the puck and score some goals.


Q.  (inaudible)

JEFF HEEREMA:  I like to say maybe Shanahan.  They gave me some kind of an indication that they might take me.  I was kind of hoping that they would and they did, so it worked out good.


